In a teleconference, Vice President Kamala Harris and Senator Tammy Duckworth discussed the importance of investing in care and caregiving in the United States. They emphasized that care and caregiving impact everyone, regardless of age, gender, or profession. They highlighted the high costs and difficulties of accessing childcare, and the need to make it more affordable and accessible. They also discussed the need to invest in home- and community-based services for seniors and people with disabilities, and to improve wages and working conditions for homecare workers. They expressed their support for the Build Back Better Agenda, which includes provisions to cut the cost of childcare, expand the Child Tax Credit, and improve options for seniors and people with disabilities. They emphasized the importance of passing this agenda to support working families and strengthen the care economy.